<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1986-10-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Infectious diseases in child day care facilities</TITLE><BODY>Abstract Infections in children in day care are common, but can be limited by education of providers and staff in standards of hygiene, maintenance of basic techniques of infection control, appropriate use of the physical facilities of the day care unit, and maintenance of recommended levels of children and staff.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>